45:40.200 --> 45:43.310
♪ Yes, it's Christmastime

45:43.510 --> 45:46.570
♪ And I wanna see Santa Claus

45:46.770 --> 45:49.190
♪ What? What? What?

45:49.380 --> 45:52.540
♪ Gonna ask him for my baby

45:52.740 --> 45:55.150
♪ Ain't that
a real good cause? ♪

45:55.350 --> 45:56.320
MRS. STEVENS:
Let me know which ones.

45:56.520 --> 45:57.890
Sure. I'll hold.

45:58.090 --> 45:59.630
MRS. MURRAY: Ah, look what
the cat dragged in.

45:59.830 --> 46:00.980
- Good afternoon, Eileen.
- [song ends]

46:01.180 --> 46:03.160
You look fresh as a daisy,
as always.

46:03.360 --> 46:04.420
I had car trouble.

46:04.620 --> 46:05.850
Yeah, I believe
the trouble part.

46:06.050 --> 46:08.200
It's almost Christmas.
Can you give me a break?

46:08.400 --> 46:10.160
No. Get to work.

46:10.360 --> 46:12.510
Okay. I need the Polk file.

46:12.710 --> 46:14.040
- [phone rings]
- Yeah.

46:14.240 --> 46:16.080
I think Dr. St. John has it.

46:16.280 --> 46:18.560
Perfect.
Yeah, I'm afraid that one

46:18.760 --> 46:20.610
will have to wait
till after the holidays.

46:20.810 --> 46:22.260
We have a new doctor on staff,

46:22.460 --> 46:24.740
and, uh, apparently she
doesn't follow procedures.

46:24.940 --> 46:26.740
- She's not in today?
- Been and gone.

46:26.940 --> 46:28.010
She's gonna be back
after Christmas.

46:28.210 --> 46:29.090
MRS. STEVENS:
Yeah. Will do.

46:29.290 --> 46:30.710
All right, then. Thank you.

46:30.900 --> 46:32.010
Bye-bye.

46:32.210 --> 46:33.750
[hangs up receiver]

46:33.950 --> 46:35.960
[Eileen sighs]

46:39.270 --> 46:41.240
Where do you think
you're going?

46:41.440 --> 46:42.720
The infirmary.

46:42.920 --> 46:44.330
I think something's
going around.

46:44.530 --> 46:46.100
MRS. MURRAY: You look like
you've been going around.

46:47.230 --> 46:48.550
She's a boozer.

46:48.750 --> 46:50.720
- [phones ringing]
- [overlapping chatter]

