49:39.540 --> 49:40.970
Dad?

49:53.070 --> 49:54.510
Dad?

50:06.260 --> 50:07.660
Dad?

50:07.860 --> 50:08.920
- Dad, can you hear me?
- [groans, muttering]

50:09.120 --> 50:10.490
Dad, can you hear me?

50:10.690 --> 50:12.270
- What were you doing up there?
- I need my gun.

50:12.470 --> 50:13.360
- Sit up.
- It's after me.

50:13.560 --> 50:14.360
Nobody's after you.

50:14.560 --> 50:16.100
Sit up. Sit up.

50:20.800 --> 50:22.490
[Jim groans]

50:25.280 --> 50:26.810
Joanie.

50:27.010 --> 50:28.670
That you, Joanie?

50:29.930 --> 50:31.860
JIM:
Hey.

50:32.060 --> 50:34.470
Joanie. Joanie.

50:34.670 --> 50:36.080
Joanie.

50:36.280 --> 50:37.780
Dad.

50:37.980 --> 50:41.000
Quit your fussing, Joanie.

50:41.200 --> 50:43.170
♪

50:52.090 --> 50:53.400
DOCTOR [voice-over]:
We stitched him up,

50:53.600 --> 50:55.010
and I don't think
he has a concussion,

50:55.210 --> 50:56.490
but his blood alcohol level

50:56.690 --> 50:58.150
is point one-seven.

50:58.350 --> 51:00.240
His liver's enlarged,
and he's covered in bruises.

51:00.430 --> 51:01.670
I'm not blaming you, honey,
but, uh...

51:01.870 --> 51:03.060
Yeah, sure.

51:03.260 --> 51:04.800
Hey, who's letting him
live like this?

51:05.000 --> 51:07.110
I don't know. My mom died,
and he doesn't have a job.

51:07.310 --> 51:08.770
What else is he supposed to do?

51:08.960 --> 51:10.420
DOCTOR: Yeah, there are men
who don't drink all day.

51:10.620 --> 51:12.250
EILEEN:
I know that.

51:12.450 --> 51:15.990
DOCTOR: Look, I know this
is hard for you, but, uh...

51:16.190 --> 51:18.300
if he stops drinking,
he might die,

51:18.500 --> 51:21.040
but if he keeps drinking,
it'll definitely kill him.

51:21.240 --> 51:23.120
I don't know what else
to say to you.

51:31.040 --> 51:32.300
Sit down, Dad.

51:41.440 --> 51:43.450
The doctor told me
you're gonna die.

51:43.650 --> 51:45.230
Oh, like he's not?

51:46.530 --> 51:48.240
He said, if you
keep drinking like this,

51:48.440 --> 51:49.500
it'll kill you.

51:49.700 --> 51:51.160
Screw him.

51:51.360 --> 51:52.590
You know they killed
your mother at that hospital.

51:52.790 --> 51:54.450
They owe me more than stitches.

51:56.020 --> 51:56.940
Can you lean back?

51:57.140 --> 51:58.290
Course I can lean back.

51:58.490 --> 52:00.300
You don't think
I know how to go to bed?

52:00.490 --> 52:01.560
[Jim grunts]

52:01.760 --> 52:03.560
Well, I need a drink.

52:03.760 --> 52:04.860
Dad!

52:05.060 --> 52:06.520
And anyway,
I do not sleep here.

52:06.720 --> 52:08.350
- It's haunted.
- Please, Dad.

52:08.550 --> 52:11.570
If I get you a bottle,
will you lie down?

52:11.770 --> 52:14.820
No. I want to have
a drink with my daughter.

52:15.780 --> 52:17.660
You're different these days.

52:17.860 --> 52:19.610
You're almost interesting.

52:21.260 --> 52:23.750
[liquid pours]

52:23.950 --> 52:26.060
[fire crackling]

52:26.260 --> 52:29.670
What are you doing with all
the money you make at work?

52:29.870 --> 52:32.070
[liquid pouring]

52:32.270 --> 52:34.230
Why don't you ever buy
your own clothes?

52:42.280 --> 52:44.430
I remember that coat.

52:44.630 --> 52:46.720
I remember your mother...

52:48.290 --> 52:50.080
How does it look on me?

52:50.280 --> 52:53.130
Well, your mother
looked beautiful in that coat.

52:53.330 --> 52:55.050
I bought it for her to wear

52:55.250 --> 52:57.470
when she got out
of the bughouse.

52:59.870 --> 53:01.830
I always loved your mother.

53:03.350 --> 53:04.790
No matter what you
thought it looked like,

53:04.990 --> 53:06.220
I always loved her.

53:08.140 --> 53:11.320
And I know
what people say about me.

53:11.520 --> 53:14.840
They say I made her crazy
'cause I'm a hard-ass.

53:17.280 --> 53:19.030
And I may have yelled
a few times,

53:19.230 --> 53:21.800
but she always forgave me.

53:24.150 --> 53:26.640
Because we loved each other.

53:26.840 --> 53:29.070
Love will make you crazy,
Eileen.

53:31.120 --> 53:33.520
You'll probably
never understand that.

53:33.720 --> 53:35.030
Why?

53:37.770 --> 53:39.830
Some people...

53:40.030 --> 53:41.690
they're the real people.

53:43.300 --> 53:46.360
Like in a movie, they're
the ones you're watching.

53:46.560 --> 53:48.480
They're the ones making moves.

53:51.180 --> 53:52.960
And the other people...

53:54.310 --> 53:57.980
...they're just there
filling the space,

53:58.180 --> 54:00.330
and you take 'em for granted.

54:00.530 --> 54:02.290
You think, "They're easy."

54:02.490 --> 54:06.190
Take a penny, leave a penny.

54:10.810 --> 54:12.720
That's you, Eileen.

54:13.680 --> 54:15.330
You're one of them.

54:18.030 --> 54:20.080
♪

54:23.340 --> 54:25.340
[fire crackling]

54:28.000 --> 54:29.390
[Jim swallows]

54:35.480 --> 54:37.710
[phone ringing]

54:37.910 --> 54:40.240
[car doors opening, closing]

54:40.440 --> 54:42.330
JIM: What are you doing?
You don't gotta lock it.

54:42.530 --> 54:44.070
- Let's go.
- [bottles clattering]

54:44.270 --> 54:45.420
- Come on. Come on.
- [ringing continues]

54:45.620 --> 54:47.200
Come on. It's cold out here.

54:47.400 --> 54:48.200
Come on. Hurry up.

54:48.400 --> 54:50.410
Open the door.

54:51.460 --> 54:53.820
[ringing continues]

54:54.020 --> 54:55.500
Fucking heavy.

55:00.290 --> 55:02.090
[ringing continues]

55:02.280 --> 55:04.300
Give me my fucking drink.

55:06.780 --> 55:08.080
[bottles clattering]

55:09.080 --> 55:11.220
- [body thuds]
- [ringing continues]

55:20.920 --> 55:23.450
[ringing continues]

55:23.650 --> 55:25.620
[water dripping]

55:30.710 --> 55:32.320
JIM:
Eileen!

55:35.760 --> 55:37.070
Eileen!

55:40.110 --> 55:41.520
What, Dad?

55:41.720 --> 55:43.130
Phone rang.

55:43.330 --> 55:44.810
Some woman looking for you.

55:45.770 --> 55:46.910
What'd you say?

55:47.110 --> 55:48.040
Nothing.

55:48.240 --> 55:51.220
I know nothing. I said nothing.

55:51.420 --> 55:52.870
[footsteps departing]

55:58.310 --> 55:59.360
Hello.

55:59.560 --> 56:01.400
REBECCA:
Hello, Christmas angel.

56:02.400 --> 56:04.150
Rebecca?

56:04.350 --> 56:06.580
Look, I was just thinking
of you,

56:06.780 --> 56:08.020
and, well, I-I don't know

56:08.220 --> 56:09.460
what you're planning
for Christmas Eve,

56:09.660 --> 56:11.460
but I thought maybe
you'd like to come over.

56:11.660 --> 56:12.900
There are some records
we could play,

56:13.090 --> 56:15.240
and maybe dance again
if all goes well.

56:17.110 --> 56:19.730
[chuckles] Unless you have
a better offer, of course.

56:19.930 --> 56:22.080
I don't have a better offer.

56:22.280 --> 56:23.820
- So you'll come?
- Yeah.

56:24.020 --> 56:25.730
Let me give you the address.

56:25.930 --> 56:27.640
Okay. Hold on.

56:30.210 --> 56:32.570
It's 32 Maple Street.

56:32.770 --> 56:35.530
So see you later.

56:35.730 --> 56:38.170
- Bye.
- Bye.

56:42.180 --> 56:44.480
["All These Things"
by Art Neville playing]

56:48.840 --> 56:52.140
♪ The touch of your lips

56:53.100 --> 56:55.930
